        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-15T18:25:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-13T18:26:00-05:00" n="1005" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1005">
                <head>Inhabitants of Thun</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thun</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1865-05-15T23:59:59+00:34" notBefore="1865-05-14T00:00:00+00:34" when="1865-05">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi>, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>The undersigned authorities, societies and private individuals in the
                        district of Thun, rejoicing over the final victory of human rights and the
                        end of the civil war in the American Union, on the one part, and lamenting
                        the murder of the greatest man in the nation, on the other hand, feel it
                        their duty to join cordially in the address to the American people and their
                        leader in the cause of freedom and humanity in our sister republic beyond
                        the ocean.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>HEINRICH HOFER, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                            <item>A. KREBSER, <hi rend="italic">Notary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>(280 other signatures.)</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
